Source: JMK via Wikimedia CommonsThis follows consultations on Tuesday, 31 January 2023, between Sanral, led by the chairman of the board, Themba Mhambi and chief executive officer, Reginald Demana, and the KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Government, as well as local government leaders, where the resumption of collection of toll fees was discussed.The Provincial Government of KwaZulu-Natal and Sanral agreed on Tuesday night that further consultations will take place shortly, following which an announcement regarding the resumption of toll fee collections will then be made.